# Deployment (Staging & Production)

**IMPORTANT**: This project is deployed on Linode Singapore servers via SSH, NOT Vercel.
There are two separate, fully isolated environments (each with its own app container + Postgres container + B2 config).

## Environments

| Environment | Domain | SSH Host | IP | Role |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Production** | `https://guided.vericant.com` | `guided-prod` | 192.46.229.162 | Live, customer-facing. Only deploy tested code. |
| **Staging** | `https://staging.guided.vericant.com` | `guided-staging` | 139.162.49.54 | Test/verify before production. |

- Both are SG (Singapore) Linode nodes. `guided-prod` was cloned from `guided-staging`.
- SSH user: `root` (SSH as root, then switch to `v0-interview` user).
- Project Path (both): `/home/v0-interview/apps/v0-interview`
- Deployment Script: `deploy-linode.sh`
- Docker Compose File: `docker-compose.linode.yml`
- App runs on port 3001 (mapped from container port 3000); Postgres on 5433.

## Per-environment configuration (do NOT mix up)

Each server has its own `.env.production`. The URL variables MUST match that server's domain:

- **Production** (`guided-prod`): `APP_URL` and `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` = `https://guided.vericant.com`
- **Staging** (`guided-staging`): `APP_URL` and `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` = `https://staging.guided.vericant.com`

Notes:
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` is baked at **build time** (Docker build arg) — changing it requires a rebuild
  (`export NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=... && docker compose -f docker-compose.linode.yml up -d --build`).
- `APP_URL` is read at **runtime** (used for email links: password reset, rater notifications) — changing it
  only requires recreating the app container (`docker compose -f docker-compose.linode.yml up -d`).
- Video/JSON files are stored on Backblaze B2; both environments currently share the same bucket
  (`New-Product-Test`). Object keys are namespaced by interview UUID so they do not collide.

## Deployment Workflow

1. **Local Development & Testing**:
   - Implement feature on a feature branch
   - Run `npm run dev` locally to test
   - Verify functionality works correctly

2. **Deploy to STAGING first** and verify:
   ```bash
   ssh guided-staging
   su - v0-interview
   cd /home/v0-interview/apps/v0-interview
   ./deploy-linode.sh
   ```
   Verify on `https://staging.guided.vericant.com`.

3. **Merge to `main`** (after staging verification passes).

4. **Deploy to PRODUCTION**:
   ```bash
   ssh guided-prod
   su - v0-interview
   cd /home/v0-interview/apps/v0-interview
   ./deploy-linode.sh
   ```
   Verify on `https://guided.vericant.com`.

## Deployment Script Actions

- Pulls latest code from `main` branch
- Stops old containers
- Builds new Docker images
- Starts PostgreSQL and application containers
- Runs Prisma database migrations (`npx prisma db push`)
- Checks application health status

## Manual Database Migration (if needed)

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.linode.yml exec -T interview-app sh -c 'npx prisma@6.19.0 db push'
```

## Verification

```bash
# Check container status
docker compose -f docker-compose.linode.yml ps

# View application logs
docker compose -f docker-compose.linode.yml logs -f interview-app

# Health check (public)
curl https://guided.vericant.com/api/health          # production
curl https://staging.guided.vericant.com/api/health  # staging
```

## Important Notes

- **Never deploy untested code directly to production** — always go through `guided-staging` first.
- Always deploy from `main` branch to production after testing on staging.
- Database migrations are run automatically via Prisma.
- If Prisma version conflicts occur, use `npx prisma@6.19.0` explicitly.
- TLS certificates are managed by Certbot (Let's Encrypt) with auto-renewal on each server.
- DNS for `*.vericant.com` is hosted on Linode DNS Manager (Networking → Domains → vericant.com).
